# Supabase Rules

## Client Setup
- Use `createServerClient` for Server Components & Server Actions
- Use `createBrowserClient` ONLY in `"use client"` components
- Never import server client in client components

## Auth Pattern
```typescript
// ✅ Correct — Server Action
import { createServerClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'

export async function getUser() {
  const supabase = await createServerClient()
  const { data: { user }, error } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
  if (error || !user) redirect('/login')
  return user
}
```

## RLS Awareness
- Prisma/Drizzle bypass RLS — always add manual auth checks in Server Actions
- Never trust client-side session for sensitive operations
- Use `service_role` only in trusted server-side admin operations
